        "updated": "2010-01-16T00:20:00Z",
        "subtitle": "<div align=\"center\"><img src=\"http://media.techeblog.com/images/penny_shooter_business_card.jpg\" /></div>\n<p>File this under: <a href=\"http://www.techeblog.com/index.php/tech-gadget/form-follows-function-when-you-ve-got-these-business-cards\">cool business cards</a>. Called the Penny Shooter, this business card isn't your average piece of paper stock, as it's capable of shooting pennies and has a 10-coin magazine. <a href=\"http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1581\" rel=\"nofollow\">More information</a>. Continue reading for the video demonstration.\n<blockquote>It has a little magazine that pops up and allows you to load up to 10 pennies. Then you can just pull back the slide and release to shoot a penny, and repeat until all the pennies are gone.</blockquote>\n<font size=\"1\">[via <a href=\"http://www.techaworld.com/strange-business-card-shoots-pennies/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tech World</a> - <a href=\"http://gizmodo.com/5449146/a-penny+shooting-business-card-probably-wont-win-anyone-over\" rel=\"nofollow\">Gizmodo</a>]</font>\n</p>",
